The paper deals with the problem of real-time status update in a cognitive radio network, which involves networked monitoring and control systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of energy consumption and the minimization of the age of information metric, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also deals with the problem of spectrum sharing, which suggests that it could belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the paper uses Markov decision processes and optimization algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MA) category.
